Speaker of the Kaduna State House of Assembly, Aminu Abdullahi Shagali, has tasked the newly appointed Commissioner for Education, Dr Shehu Muhammad Usman Makarfi, to tackle rising rape cases in schools across the state. The Speaker made the call shortly after confirming the nominee for the position. He said the issue of rape in schools was worrisome and that even parents are very disturbed. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “Dr Shehu Makarfi, if confirmed, try and tackle the rising cases of rape in schools, including Islamiyya schools, please”, he said. Daily Trust on Sunday gathered that there have been reported cases of teachers raping pupils in some schools. Earlier, Dr Shehu Muhammad Makarfi said transforming the educational system is the responsibility of all citizens. He expressed his readiness to ensure that the standard of education in the state improves. Dr Makarfi, who was the Permanent Secretary in the Ministry of Health, lamented the proliferation of private schools across the state, saying a mechanism will be introduced to checkmate their activities. Tackle rape cases in schools, Kaduna speaker begs new Commissioner Three lecturers kidnapped in Kaduna Kaduna to revoke licences of unregistered schools Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin